Installation

To run the TaskMaster project on your local machine, follow these steps:

    Clone the project from GitHub: git clone https://github.com/abhi7275/TaskMaster.git
    Navigate to the project directory: cd TaskMaster
    Compile the source code: g++ -c main.cpp -o main.o
    Compile the algorithm code: g++ -c algo.cpp -o algo.o
    Link the object files: g++ main.o algo.o -o taskmaster
    Run the application: ./taskmaster

Usage

The TaskMaster application provides a command-line menu with the following options:

    Add Task: Allows users to add a new task, providing details such as name, description, due date, priority, and completion status.

    Edit Task: Enables users to edit the details of an existing task by specifying its ID.

    List Tasks: Lists all tasks currently stored in the application.

    Search Tasks: Searches for tasks based on a keyword in the task's name, description, or category.

    Set Reminder: Allows users to set a reminder for a specific task, specifying the number of minutes before the due date.

    Quit: Exits the TaskMaster application.

Project Structure

The project is structured as follows:

    main.cpp: Contains the main program, menu, and user interaction logic.
    algo.cpp: Contains the core logic for adding, editing, listing, searching, and setting reminders for tasks.
    algo.h: Header file defining function prototypes and the Task structure.
    README.md: Project documentation.
    LICENSE: License information.

Features
Implemented Features

    Adding new tasks with details such as name, description, due date, priority, and completion status.
    Editing existing tasks by specifying the task ID.
    Listing all tasks stored in the application.
    Searching for tasks based on a keyword in task names, descriptions, or categories.
    Setting reminders for tasks to trigger at a specified time before the due date.

Future Improvements

    Task recurrence feature to support recurring tasks.
    Graphical user interface (GUI) for a more user-friendly experience.
